        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our sensitivity requirement is driven by the need to measure dust masses below 10 Earth masses, which are reasonable upper limits for the masses of dusty debris disks. This sets a goal sensitivity of 0.025 mJy/beam. The source size is unknown, but an upper limit of 0.8'' in radius suggests a resolution of 1.6'' or somewhat less for our observations will be sufficient to regard it as a point-source. The wavelength of 1mm is chosen because of the steep fall-off of dust emission at longer wavelengths. The expected continuum level of 0.1 mJy/beam is provided as a guess value, as we are probing such low dust masses that previous data offer little guidance.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
